dataIdInfo.idPurp:
A common coastline for the Eastern North America derived from the CanVec 1:50,000 coastline. Long rivers and inlets, (e.g. St. John River, NB) have been clipped near the coast.
The data source for the New England states is https://gadm.org/. The scale for this dataset is unknown.
